Voyager New Moves

Psychic Terrain

Type Category PP Power Accuracy Description
10 0 The ground turns weird for 5 turns. Blocks priority.

In the Field

If a Pokemon in your party knows or can learn Psychic Terrain, then you can activate it to sense incoming attacks from wild Pokemon.
With Psychic Terrain active, you'll have the option to ignore any wild Pokemon encounters. Battles that begin while this effect is active will have active Psychic Terrain in the battle.
There is no cost to deploy the Psychic Terrain, but it will tax your party to keep it active over time. Each time you would encounter a wild Pokemon, the Pokemon that deployed the terrain will lose PP if it currently knows the move, or will lose HP if it does not.
You can remove the Psychic Terrain effect at any time by using it again from the party menu. The effect will also be removed if the Pokemon who used it faints.
You will unlock the ability to use Psychic Terrain in the field between Gym 3 and Gym 4. Check the walkthrough for details!
